  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Radiochemotherapy is a standard for the treatment of unresectable stage III non-small cell
      lung cancer. The investigators goal is to study the efficacy and the toxicity for a promising
      association of new agents (cetuximab and pemetrexed) with concurrent radiotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
